sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team
    participant F as Finance
    participant IT as IT Ops

    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    S->>F: Credit check request
    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION — Added risk assessment decision with expedited path for low-risk customers
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Score >750, Verified Co., Clean History?)

    alt Low-Risk (Score >750 AND Verified AND No Payment Issues)
        F-->>S: Auto-Approved – Low Risk (expedited)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (expedited path)
    else High-Risk
        F->>F: Escalate to Finance Director
        F-->>S: Finance Director Approval (24h SLA)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts
    end
    %% END CHANGED SECTION
    IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Replaced the single Finance approval step with a risk assessment decision point inside Finance. An `alt`/`else` block now branches the flow: low-risk customers (credit score >750, verified company status, no payment history issues) receive automatic approval and proceed directly to account provisioning via an expedited path, while high-risk customers are escalated to the Finance Director for the existing 24h SLA approval workflow. Both paths converge at account provisioning and continue through the same welcome/login/kickoff sequence.